WEBVTT

00:26.820 --> 00:28.920
CHAPTER XXIII.

00:30.400 --> 00:36.360
Thou shalt not raise a false report, put not thine hand with a wicked to be an unrighteous

00:36.360 --> 00:36.900
witness.

00:38.080 --> 00:43.620
Thou shalt not follow a multitude to do evil, neither shalt thou speak in a cause to decline

00:43.620 --> 00:49.660
after many to rest judgment, neither shalt thou countenance a poor man in his cause.

00:50.860 --> 00:56.100
If thou meet thine enemy's ox or his ass going astray, thou shalt surely bring it back

00:56.100 --> 00:57.000
to him again.

00:57.600 --> 01:03.060
If thou see the ass of him that hateth thee lying under his burden, and wouldest forbear

01:03.060 --> 01:06.080
to help him, thou shalt surely help with him.

01:06.760 --> 01:10.140
Thou shalt not rest the judgment of thy poor in his cause.

01:11.320 --> 01:16.700
Keep thee far from a false matter, and the innocent and righteous slay thou not, for

01:16.700 --> 01:18.600
I will not justify the wicked.

01:19.580 --> 01:25.040
And thou shalt take no gift, for the gift blindeth the wise and perverteth the words

01:25.040 --> 01:25.900
of the righteous.

01:27.080 --> 01:33.040
Also thou shalt not oppress a stranger, for ye know the heart of a stranger seeing ye

01:33.040 --> 01:35.100
were strangers in the land of Egypt.

01:36.140 --> 01:41.820
In six years thou shalt sow thy land and shalt gather in the fruits thereof, but the seventh

01:41.820 --> 01:47.840
year thou shalt let it rest and lie still, that the poor of thy people may eat, and what

01:47.840 --> 01:50.240
they leave the beasts of the field shall eat.

01:50.820 --> 01:55.220
In like manner thou shalt deal with thy vineyard and with thy olive-yard.

01:56.600 --> 02:02.160
Six days thou shalt do thy work, and on the seventh day thou shalt rest, that thine ox

02:02.160 --> 02:07.740
and thine ass may rest, and the son of thy handmaid and the stranger may be refreshed.

02:08.540 --> 02:13.680
And in all things that I have said unto you, be circumspect, and make no mention of the

02:13.680 --> 02:17.640
name of other gods, neither let it be heard out of thy mouth.

02:19.200 --> 02:22.840
Three times thou shalt keep a feast unto me in the year.

02:23.580 --> 02:28.640
Thou shalt keep the feast of unleavened bread, thou shalt eat unleavened bread seven days

02:28.640 --> 02:34.700
as I commanded thee in the time appointed of the month Abib, for in it thou camest out

02:34.700 --> 02:38.000
from Egypt, and none shall appear before me empty.

02:38.820 --> 02:47.040
And the feast of harvest, the first fruits of thy labors, which thou hast sown in the

02:47.040 --> 02:52.940
year, when thou hast gathered in thy labors out of the field, three times in the year

02:52.940 --> 02:56.280
all thy males shall appear before the Lord God.

02:57.720 --> 03:03.020
Thou shalt not offer the blood of my sacrifice with leavened bread, neither shall the fat

03:03.020 --> 03:05.660
of my sacrifice remain until the morning.

03:06.680 --> 03:11.080
The first of the first fruits of thy land thou shalt bring into the house of the Lord

03:11.080 --> 03:11.780
thy God.

03:12.520 --> 03:15.480
Thou shalt not see the kid in his mother's milk.

03:17.340 --> 03:22.620
Behold, I send an angel before thee to keep thee in the way, and to bring thee into the

03:22.620 --> 03:24.120
place which I have prepared.

03:24.960 --> 03:31.240
Beware of him, and obey his voice, provoke him not, for he will not pardon your transgressions,

03:31.640 --> 03:33.200
for my name is in him.

03:33.880 --> 03:40.080
But if thou shalt indeed obey his voice, and do all that I speak, then I will be an enemy

03:40.080 --> 03:44.160
unto thine enemies, and an adversary unto thine adversaries.

03:45.100 --> 03:50.260
For mine angel shall go before thee, and bring thee in unto the Amorites, and the Hittites,

03:50.280 --> 03:55.520
and the Perizzites, and the Canaanites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, and I will

03:55.520 --> 03:56.480
cut them off.

03:57.360 --> 04:03.680
Thou shalt not bow down to their gods, nor serve them, nor do after their works, but

04:03.680 --> 04:07.740
thou shalt utterly overthrow them, and quite break down their images.

04:08.300 --> 04:14.120
And ye shall serve the Lord your God, and he shall bless thy bread and thy water, and

04:14.120 --> 04:16.960
I will take sickness away from the midst of thee.

04:18.300 --> 04:23.960
There shall nothing cast their young nor be barren in thy land the number of thy days

04:23.960 --> 04:25.080
I will fulfill.

04:26.080 --> 04:31.060
I will send my fear before thee, and will destroy all the people to whom thou shalt

04:31.060 --> 04:35.280
come, and I will make all thine enemies turn their backs unto thee.

04:35.960 --> 04:41.180
And I will send hornets before thee, which shall drive out the Hivite, the Canaanite,

04:41.180 --> 04:43.240
and the Hittite from before thee.

04:44.000 --> 04:49.000
I will not drive them out from before thee in one year, lest the land become desolate,

04:49.320 --> 04:52.120
and the beasts of the field multiply against thee.

04:52.900 --> 04:58.140
By little and little I will drive them out from before thee, until thou be increased

04:58.140 --> 04:59.740
and inherit the land.

05:00.280 --> 05:05.860
And I will set thy bounds from the Red Sea, even unto the Sea of the Philistines, and

05:05.860 --> 05:07.780
from the desert unto the river.

05:08.180 --> 05:12.920
For I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and thou shalt drive

05:12.920 --> 05:14.340
them out before thee.

05:15.320 --> 05:19.060
Thou shalt make no covenant with them, nor with their gods.

05:20.000 --> 05:25.240
They shall not dwell in thy land, lest they make thee sin against me, for if thou serve

05:25.240 --> 05:28.800
their gods, it will surely be a snare unto thee.

05:30.060 --> 05:35.080
Chapter 24 And he said unto Moses, Come up unto the

05:35.080 --> 05:41.600
Lord, thou and Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and Seventy, of the elders of Israel, and worship

05:41.600 --> 05:42.740
ye far off.

05:43.540 --> 05:48.680
And Moses alone shall come near the Lord, but they shall not come nigh, neither shall

05:48.680 --> 05:50.300
the people go up with him.

05:51.660 --> 05:57.120
And Moses came and told the people all the words of the Lord, and all the judgments,

05:57.420 --> 06:02.860
and all the people answered with one voice, and said, All the words which the Lord hath

06:02.860 --> 06:04.420
said, will we do.

06:05.520 --> 06:10.920
And Moses wrote all the words of the Lord, and rose up early in the morning, and build

06:10.920 --> 06:16.520
it an altar under the hill, and twelve pillars according to the twelve tribes of Israel.

06:17.400 --> 06:23.140
And he sent young men of the children of Israel, which offered burnt offerings, and sacrificed

06:23.140 --> 06:26.040
peace offerings of oxen unto the Lord.

06:27.660 --> 06:32.900
And Moses took half of the blood, and put it in basins, and half of the blood he sprinkled

06:32.900 --> 06:33.680
on the altar.

06:34.580 --> 06:39.320
And he took the book of the covenant, and read in the audience of the people, and they

06:39.320 --> 06:43.780
said, All that the Lord hath said, will we do, and be obedient.

06:44.920 --> 06:50.460
And Moses took the blood, and sprinkled it on the people, and said, Behold the blood

06:50.460 --> 06:54.920
of the covenant, which the Lord hath made with you concerning all these words.

06:56.300 --> 07:02.800
Then went up Moses and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel, and they

07:02.800 --> 07:08.380
saw the God of Israel, and there was under his feet, as it were, a paved work of a sapphire

07:08.380 --> 07:12.260
stone, and as it were, the body of heaven in his clearness.

07:13.500 --> 07:19.800
And upon the nobles of the children of Israel he laid not his hand, also they saw God, and

07:19.800 --> 07:21.220
did eat and drink.

07:22.520 --> 07:28.440
And the Lord said unto Moses, Come up to me into the mount, and be there, and I will

07:28.440 --> 07:34.380
give thee tables of stone, and a law and commandments which I have written, that thou mayest teach

07:34.380 --> 07:34.800
them.

07:35.500 --> 07:41.600
And Moses rose up, and his minister Joshua, and Moses went up into the mount of God.

07:42.360 --> 07:48.140
And he said unto the elders, Terry ye here for us, until we come again unto you, and

07:48.140 --> 07:54.180
behold Aaron and her are with you, if any man have any matters to do, let him come unto

07:54.180 --> 07:54.640
them.

07:55.840 --> 07:59.720
And Moses went up into the mount, and a cloud covered the mount.

08:00.400 --> 08:06.260
And the glory of the Lord abode upon Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it six days,

08:06.540 --> 08:10.540
and the seventh day he called unto Moses out of the midst of the cloud.

08:11.760 --> 08:16.580
And the sight of the glory of the Lord was like devouring fire on the top of the mount

08:16.580 --> 08:19.040
in the eyes of the children of Israel.

08:20.080 --> 08:25.680
And Moses went into the midst of the cloud, and got him up into the mount, and Moses was

08:25.680 --> 08:28.600
in the mount forty days and forty nights.

08:30.920 --> 08:36.380
Chapter 25 And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Speak

08:36.380 --> 08:41.320
unto the children of Israel that they bring me an offering, of every man that giveth it

08:41.320 --> 08:44.000
willingly with his heart he shall take my offering.

08:44.760 --> 08:50.840
And this is the offering which he shall take of them, gold and silver and brass, and blue

08:50.840 --> 08:58.240
and purple and scarlet and fine linen and goat's hair and ram's skins dyed red and badger's

08:58.580 --> 09:05.780
skins and shittim wood, oil for the light, spices for anointing oil and for sweet incense,

09:06.620 --> 09:12.380
onyx stones and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate, and let them make

09:12.380 --> 09:15.400
me a sanctuary that I may dwell among them.

09:16.480 --> 09:21.740
According to all that I show thee, after the pattern of the tabernacle, and the pattern

09:21.740 --> 09:26.080
of all the instruments thereof, even so shall ye make it.

09:28.180 --> 09:33.300
And they shall make an ark of shittim wood, two cubits and a half shall be the length

09:33.300 --> 09:38.340
thereof, and a cubit and a half the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height

09:38.340 --> 09:39.060
thereof.

09:39.060 --> 09:44.760
And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, within and without shalt thou overlay it,

09:45.140 --> 09:48.180
and shalt make upon it a crown of gold round about.

09:49.060 --> 09:54.160
And thou shalt cast four rings of gold for it, and put them in the four corners thereof,

09:54.540 --> 09:59.020
and two rings shall be in the one side of it, and two rings in the other side of it.

10:00.000 --> 10:04.260
And thou shalt make staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.

10:04.880 --> 10:09.880
And thou shalt put the staves into the rings by the sides of the ark that the ark may be

10:09.880 --> 10:10.860
borne with them.

10:11.540 --> 10:16.000
The staves shall be in the rings of the ark, they shall not be taken from it.

10:16.660 --> 10:20.480
And thou shalt put into the ark the testimony which I shall give thee.

10:21.380 --> 10:26.620
And thou shalt make a mercy-seat of pure gold, two cubits and a half shall be the length

10:26.620 --> 10:30.000
thereof, and a cubit and a half the breadth thereof.

10:30.680 --> 10:36.060
And thou shalt make two cherubims of gold, of beaten work, shalt thou make them in the

10:36.060 --> 10:37.600
two ends of the mercy-seat.

10:38.520 --> 10:43.540
And make one cherub on the one end, and the other cherub on the other end, even of the

10:43.540 --> 10:47.200
mercy-seat shall ye make the cherubims on the two ends thereof.

10:48.180 --> 10:53.100
And the cherubims shall stretch forth their wings on high, covering the mercy-seat with

10:53.100 --> 10:58.520
their wings, and their faces shall look one to another, toward the mercy-seat shall the

10:58.520 --> 11:00.440
faces of the cherubims be.

11:01.460 --> 11:06.660
And thou shalt put the mercy-seat above upon the ark, and in the ark thou shalt put the

11:06.660 --> 11:08.480
testimony that I shall give thee.

11:09.200 --> 11:14.100
And there I will meet with thee, and I will commune with thee from above the mercy-seat,

11:14.380 --> 11:19.780
from between the two cherubims which are upon the ark of the testimony of all things which

11:19.780 --> 11:23.180
I will give thee in commandment unto the children of Israel.

11:24.780 --> 11:30.500
Thou shalt also make a table of shittim wood, two cubits shall be the length thereof, and

11:30.500 --> 11:34.580
a cubit the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height thereof.

11:35.500 --> 11:40.960
And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, and make thereto a crown of gold round about.

11:41.880 --> 11:46.660
And thou shalt make unto it a border of an hand-breadth round about, and thou shalt make

11:46.660 --> 11:49.520
a golden crown to the border thereof round about.

11:50.080 --> 11:55.380
And thou shalt make for it four rings of gold, and put the rings in the four corners that

11:55.380 --> 11:57.120
are on the four feet thereof.

11:58.080 --> 12:02.960
Over against the border shall the rings be for places of the staves to bear the table.

12:03.900 --> 12:08.400
And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold that the

12:08.400 --> 12:10.120
table may be borne with them.

12:10.740 --> 12:16.320
And thou shalt make the dishes thereof, and spoons thereof, and covers thereof, and bowls

12:16.320 --> 12:20.740
thereof, to cover with all, of pure gold shalt thou make them.

12:21.360 --> 12:25.120
And thou shalt set upon the table showbread before me all way.

12:26.180 --> 12:31.040
And thou shalt make a candlestick of pure gold, of beaten work shall the candlestick

12:31.040 --> 12:37.540
be made, his shaft and his branches, his bowls, his knops, and his flowers shall be of the

12:37.540 --> 12:37.860
same.

12:38.980 --> 12:44.140
And six branches shall come out of the sides of it, three branches of the candlestick out

12:44.140 --> 12:48.600
of the one side, and three branches of the candlestick out of the other side.

12:48.960 --> 12:54.540
Three bowls made like unto almonds, with a knop and a flower in one branch, and three

12:54.540 --> 12:58.340
bowls made like almonds in the other branch, with a knop and a flower.

12:58.880 --> 13:02.140
So in the six branches that come out of the candlestick.

13:03.220 --> 13:08.020
And in the candlestick shall be four bowls made like unto almonds, with their knops and

13:08.020 --> 13:08.820
their flowers.

13:08.820 --> 13:14.200
And there shall be a knop under two branches of the same, and a knop under two branches

13:14.200 --> 13:19.340
of the same, and a knop under two branches of the same, according to the six branches

13:19.340 --> 13:21.420
that proceed out of the candlestick.

13:22.060 --> 13:25.040
Their knops and their branches shall be of the same.

13:25.680 --> 13:28.540
All it shall be one beaten work of pure gold.

13:29.300 --> 13:34.160
And thou shalt make the seven lamps thereof, and they shall light the lamps thereof, that

13:34.160 --> 13:36.360
they may give light over against it.

13:36.870 --> 13:41.500
And the tongs thereof, and the snuff-dishes thereof, shall be of pure gold.

13:42.540 --> 13:46.480
Of a talent of pure gold shall he make it with all these vessels.

13:47.380 --> 13:52.040
And look that thou maketh them after their pattern which was shewed thee in the mount.

13:55.320 --> 13:56.400
CHAPTER XXVI.

13:56.840 --> 14:02.040
Moreover thou shalt make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine twined linen, and blue

14:02.040 --> 14:07.020
and purple and scarlet, with cherubims of cunning work shalt thou make them.

14:08.160 --> 14:12.860
The length of one curtain shall be eight and twenty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain

14:12.860 --> 14:16.700
four cubits, and every one of the curtains shall have one measure.

14:17.920 --> 14:23.220
The five curtains shall be coupled together one to another, and other five curtains shall

14:23.220 --> 14:24.760
be coupled one to another.

14:25.500 --> 14:30.140
And thou shalt make loops of blue upon the edge of the one curtain from the selvedge

14:30.140 --> 14:35.480
in the coupling, and likewise shalt thou make in the uttermost edge of another curtain in

14:35.480 --> 14:36.740
the coupling of the second.

14:37.920 --> 14:43.140
Fifty loops shalt thou make in the one curtain, and fifty loops shalt thou make in the edge

14:43.140 --> 14:48.060
of the curtain that is in the coupling of the second, that the loops may take hold one

14:48.060 --> 14:48.640
of another.

14:49.780 --> 14:54.760
And thou shalt make fifty tashes of gold, and couple the curtains together with the

14:54.760 --> 14:57.620
tashes, and it shall be one tabernacle.

14:58.780 --> 15:04.080
And thou shalt make curtains of goat's hair to be a covering upon the tabernacle, eleven

15:04.080 --> 15:05.780
curtains shalt thou make.

15:06.660 --> 15:11.320
The length of one curtain shall be thirty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four

15:11.320 --> 15:14.920
cubits, and the eleven curtains shall be all of one measure.

15:16.180 --> 15:21.800
And thou shalt couple five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves, and shalt

15:21.800 --> 15:24.980
double the sixth curtain in the forefront of the tabernacle.

15:25.900 --> 15:30.640
And thou shalt make fifty loops on the edge of the one curtain that is outmost in the

15:30.640 --> 15:35.040
coupling, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain which coupleth the second.

15:35.920 --> 15:41.280
And thou shalt make fifty tashes of brass, and put the tashes into the loops, and couple

15:41.280 --> 15:43.660
the tent together, that it may be one.

15:45.980 --> 15:50.440
And the remnant of that remaineth that the curtains of the tent, the half-curtain that

15:50.440 --> 15:53.660
remaineth, shall hang over the backside of the tabernacle.

15:54.200 --> 15:59.260
And a cubit on the one side, and a cubit on the other side, of that which remaineth in

15:59.260 --> 16:03.860
the length of the curtains of the tent, it shall hang over the sides of the tabernacle,

16:04.180 --> 16:07.080
on this side, and on that side, to cover it.

16:08.200 --> 16:13.400
And thou shalt make a covering for the tent of ram-skins dyed red, and a covering above

16:13.400 --> 16:14.660
of badger's skins.

16:15.480 --> 16:19.840
And thou shalt make boards for the tabernacle of shittim wood standing up.

16:20.560 --> 16:24.960
Ten cubits shall be the length of a board, and a cubit and a half shall be the breadth

16:24.960 --> 16:25.820
of one board.

16:26.860 --> 16:32.780
Two tenons shall there be in one board, set in order one against another, thus shalt thou

16:32.780 --> 16:35.120
make for all the boards of the tabernacle.

16:35.920 --> 16:41.060
And thou shalt make the boards for the tabernacle twenty boards on the south side southward.

16:41.560 --> 16:47.080
And thou shalt make forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards, two sockets under

16:47.080 --> 16:52.340
one board for his two tenons, and two sockets under another board for his two tenons.

16:53.040 --> 16:57.720
And for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, there shall be twenty boards.

16:58.200 --> 17:04.320
And there are forty sockets of silver, two sockets under one board, and two sockets under

17:04.320 --> 17:05.160
another board.

17:05.860 --> 17:10.080
And for the sides of the tabernacle westward, thou shalt make six boards.

17:10.560 --> 17:15.120
And two boards shalt thou make for the corners of the tabernacle and the two sides.

17:15.720 --> 17:19.800
And they shall be coupled together beneath, and they shall be coupled together above the

17:19.800 --> 17:25.660
head of it onto one ring, thus shall it be for them both, they shall be for the two corners.

17:26.440 --> 17:32.000
And they shall be eight boards, and their sockets of silver sixteen sockets, two sockets

17:32.000 --> 17:35.480
under one board, and two sockets under another board.

17:36.520 --> 17:44.640
And thou shalt make bars of shittim wood, five for the boards of the one side of the

17:44.640 --> 17:49.900
tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle for the two sides

17:49.900 --> 17:50.620
westward.

17:51.180 --> 17:55.380
And the middle bar in the midst of the boards shall reach from end to end.

17:56.060 --> 18:01.060
And thou shalt overlay the boards with gold, and make their rings of gold for places for

18:01.060 --> 18:04.540
the bars, and thou shalt overlay the bars with gold.

18:05.200 --> 18:09.740
And thou shalt rear up the tabernacle according to the fashion thereof which was shewed thee

18:09.740 --> 18:10.420
in the mount.

18:11.360 --> 18:17.240
And thou shalt make a veil of blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen of cunning

18:17.240 --> 18:20.160
work with cherubims shall it be made.

18:20.720 --> 18:25.900
And thou shalt hang it upon four pillars of shittim wood overlaid with gold, their hooks

18:25.900 --> 18:28.820
shall be of gold upon the four sockets of silver.

18:29.760 --> 18:34.680
And thou shalt hang up the veil under the tashes that thou mayest bring in thither within

18:34.680 --> 18:39.820
the veil the ark of the testimony, and the veil shall divide unto you between the holy

18:39.820 --> 18:41.320
place and the most holy.

18:42.180 --> 18:47.040
And thou shalt put the mercy seat upon the ark of the testimony in the most holy place.

18:47.740 --> 18:52.880
And thou shalt set the table without the veil and the candlestick over against the table

18:52.880 --> 18:55.580
on the side of the tabernacle toward the south.

18:56.140 --> 18:58.480
And thou shalt put the table on the north side.

18:59.360 --> 19:04.540
And thou shalt make an hanging for the door of the tent of blue and purple and scarlet

19:04.540 --> 19:07.580
and fine twined linen wrought with needlework.

19:08.230 --> 19:13.520
And thou shalt make for the hanging five pillars of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold,

19:13.840 --> 19:15.580
and their hooks shall be of gold.

19:15.920 --> 19:18.980
And thou shalt cast five sockets of brass for them.

19:20.960 --> 19:22.120
CHAPTER XXVII.

19:22.740 --> 19:27.680
And thou shalt make an altar of shittim wood, five cubits long and five cubits broad.

19:28.140 --> 19:32.380
The altar shall be four square, and the height thereof shall be three cubits.

19:33.080 --> 19:36.840
And thou shalt make the horns of it upon the four corners thereof.

19:37.180 --> 19:41.300
His horns shall be of the same, and thou shalt overlay it with brass.

19:42.140 --> 19:47.360
And thou shalt make his pans to receive his ashes, and his shovels, and his basins, and

19:47.360 --> 19:52.920
his flesh-hooks, and his fire-pans, all the vessels thereof thou shalt make of brass.

19:53.920 --> 19:59.160
And thou shalt make for it a great of network of brass, and upon the net shalt thou make

19:59.160 --> 20:02.320
four brazen rings, in the four corners thereof.

20:02.920 --> 20:07.640
And thou shalt put it under the compass of the altar beneath, that the net may be even

20:07.640 --> 20:09.060
to the midst of the altar.

20:09.920 --> 20:14.840
And thou shalt make staves for the altar, staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with

20:14.840 --> 20:15.400
brass.

20:15.960 --> 20:20.760
And the staves shall be put into the rings, and the staves shall be upon the two sides

20:20.760 --> 20:22.340
of the altar, to bear it.

20:23.500 --> 20:25.460
Hollow with boards shalt thou make it.

20:25.460 --> 20:29.100
As it was shewed thee in the mount, so shall they make it.

20:29.800 --> 20:34.980
And thou shalt make the court of the tabernacle, for the south side southward there shall be

20:34.980 --> 20:40.940
hangings for the court of fine twine linen of an hundred cubits long for one side, and

20:40.940 --> 20:46.000
the twenty pillars thereof and their twenty sockets shall be of brass, the hooks of the

20:46.000 --> 20:48.360
pillars and their fillets shall be of silver.

20:49.440 --> 20:54.220
And likewise for the north side in length there shall be hangings of an hundred cubits

20:54.220 --> 20:59.940
long, and his twenty pillars and their twenty sockets of brass, the hooks of the pillars

20:59.940 --> 21:01.480
and their fillets of silver.

21:02.600 --> 21:07.680
And for the breadth of the court on the west side shall be hangings of fifty cubits, their

21:07.680 --> 21:09.920
pillars ten and their sockets ten.

21:10.800 --> 21:15.200
And the breadth of the court on the east side eastward shall be fifty cubits.

21:15.660 --> 21:20.880
The hangings of one side of the gate shall be fifteen cubits, their pillars three and

21:20.880 --> 21:22.140
their sockets three.

21:22.940 --> 21:28.780
And on the other side shall be hangings fifteen cubits, their pillars three and their sockets

21:28.780 --> 21:29.280
three.

21:30.160 --> 21:35.220
And for the gate of the court shall be in hanging of twenty cubits of blue and purple

21:35.220 --> 21:41.260
and scarlet and fine twine linen wrought with needlework, and their pillars shall be four

21:41.260 --> 21:42.700
and their sockets four.

21:43.760 --> 21:48.540
All the pillars round about the court shall be filleted with silver, their hooks shall

21:48.540 --> 21:51.000
be of silver and their sockets of brass.

21:52.420 --> 21:57.760
The length of the court shall be in hundred cubits and the breadth fifty everywhere and

21:57.760 --> 22:02.200
the height five cubits of fine twine linen and their sockets of brass.

22:03.240 --> 22:08.500
All the vessels of the tabernacle and all the service thereof and all the pins thereof

22:08.500 --> 22:11.620
and all the pins of the court shall be of brass.

22:12.720 --> 22:17.920
And thou shalt command the children of Israel that they bring the pure oil olive beaten

22:17.920 --> 22:21.320
for the light, to cause the lamp to burn always.

22:22.340 --> 22:28.060
In the tabernacle of the congregation, without the veil which is before the testimony, Aaron

22:28.060 --> 22:32.140
and his sons shall order it from evening to morning before the Lord.

22:32.620 --> 22:37.720
It shall be a statute for ever unto their generations on the behalf of the children

22:37.720 --> 22:38.360
of Israel.

